RFC draft-ietf-httpbis-alt-svc-06

a different protocol configuration used to access the same resources with the Origin.
Main enhancement includes the ALTSVC header,An Application Layer Protocol Negotiation (ALPN) protocol,host,port,freshness lifetime.
Illustrated a little below:
  An HTTP(S) origin server can advertise the availability of
   alternative services to clients by adding an Alt-Svc header field to
   responses.
  such as optional new host and new port,new protocol
  
    The Alt-Used header field is used in requests to indicate the
   identity of the alternative service in use, just as the Host header
   field (Section 5.4 of [RFC7230]) identifies the host and port of the
   origin.
  

